        {
          "type": "text_block",
          "settings": {
            "text_content": "<p><strong>What if you could whiten your teeth in ten minutes a day — hands-free, while you do your makeup?</strong></p><p>I used to think whiter teeth meant the dentist's chair. I'd paid for in-chair whitening more than once: $600-plus a visit, a couple of hours sitting still, and days of sensitivity afterwards. Every hot or cold drink was a reminder.</p><p>I tried the supermarket strips too. They slip around, they're fiddly, and for me they stung — that sharp zinger you get from peroxide.</p><p>So my teeth went back to how they were, and I went back to hiding them in photos.</p><p><strong>Then a friend showed me how she was doing it at home.</strong></p><p>She wasn't sitting still with her mouth open. She had a small LED tray in, hands free, doing her makeup — ten minutes, then rinse. Peroxide-free gel, no sting. She'd photographed her teeth against a shade card on day one and checked it every Sunday.</p><p>For less than one in-chair visit, I could own the device and simply reorder the gel. Three days later, mine arrived.</p>",
