        {
          "type": "text_block",
          "settings": {
            "text_content": "<p>When my kit arrived, I did the thing they tell you to do: I photographed my teeth against the shade card on day one, in the same bathroom light. Not the most flattering photo, but that was the point — I wanted an honest starting line.</p><p>The first few days, my teeth felt cleaner and smoother. By the end of the first week, the shade card had shifted a notch. No sensitivity, no zingers — I just did my ten minutes while I got ready.</p><p>Around day 14, a friend asked if I'd had my teeth done. That was the moment it felt real.</p><p>By day 30 I put the two shade-card photos side by side. The difference was clear to me — though everyone's teeth start in a different place, so individual results vary. What I liked most was how little I had to think about it.</p>",
