        {
          "type": "text_block",
          "settings": {
            "text_content": "<p>Whitening isn't a one-and-done thing — stains come back with coffee, tea, wine and time. So the system is built around a small refill, not a big one-off purchase.</p><p>You start with the device and your first gel. After that, a two-syringe refill lands every five weeks — about the rate you actually use it — for $29. That prices the device itself at an effective $20, because most of what you pay over time is simply the gel.</p><p>There's no lock-in. You can skip, pause, change quantity or cancel from your account in a couple of clicks — no emails, no phone calls.</p>",
