        {
          "type": "text_block",
          "settings": {
            "text_content": "<p><strong>Whitening strips:</strong> They can work, but they slip around and the peroxide makes a lot of people wince — and they're fiddly to keep on for the contact time they need.</p><p><strong>In-chair whitening:</strong> Effective, but it's $600 or more a visit, time in the chair, and often days of sensitivity afterwards.</p><p><strong>Cheap LED kits:</strong> The light is the easy part. Without decent gel and a tray that actually holds, you're mostly buying a blue night light.</p><p><strong>[Brand]:</strong> Peroxide-free PAP+ gel, a hands-free tray, and ten minutes a day while you get ready. Refills land on their own, and you can skip, pause or cancel in 2 clicks.</p>",
